+# Selector - exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit / run-001
+
+## Selected Portfolio
+
+1. Chain 04 - Definition-Stability Audit for "Near-Closed Tao Circuit"
+2. Chain 02 - Spectator-Leakage Lower-Bound Ledger
+3. Chain 03 - Adversarial Near-Circuit Construction Search
+
+These three make the strongest portfolio because they cover the full mission risk surface without collapsing into one obstruction style. Chain 04 is the prerequisite gatekeeper: if the object is unstable or circular, later theorem work is fake. Chain 02 then attacks the inherited exact-NS non-isolability pressure in its most mission-aligned quantitative form, and it still pays off on failure because a vanishing-leakage family would become explicit anti-obstruction evidence. Chain 03 preserves the highest-upside adversarial route by directly trying to beat the obstruction with an exact small packet, so the portfolio does not overfit to one no-circuit narrative.
+
+## Full Ranking
+
+### 1. Chain 04 - Definition-Stability Audit for "Near-Closed Tao Circuit"
+
+Best first choice because it forces the mission object to survive invariance, normalization, and edge-case audits before any theorem rhetoric begins. It has the strongest early kill condition and the highest value even in failure, since a sharp definition-level obstruction is itself an allowed success state.
+
+### 2. Chain 02 - Spectator-Leakage Lower-Bound Ledger
+
+Best positive-obstruction route after Chain 04 because it directly targets the inherited pressure that exact NS cannot isolate Tao's five-role circuit. It is broader and more mission-central than a pure coefficient-rigidity claim, and if the lower bound fails it still produces an explicit low-leakage family that usefully feeds the adversarial construction path.
+
+### 3. Chain 03 - Adversarial Near-Circuit Construction Search
+
+Required to preserve a genuine negative-kill path. It is the highest-upside chain in the portfolio, and even on failure it returns a ranked failure atlas for small exact packets rather than an empty search narrative.
+
+### 4. Chain 01 - Minimal Helical Coefficient-Rigidity Theorem
+
+Strong and clean, but ranked fourth because it is the narrowest obstruction route and the most brittle to geometric escape hatches. If the ratio-rigidity thesis breaks, its likely value is mostly diagnostic redirection into the leakage and construction routes already covered by Chains 02 and 03, so it adds less portfolio diversity than those alternatives.
+
+## Selected File Mapping
+
+- `selected/chain-01.md` contains planner `Chain 04`
+- `selected/chain-02.md` contains planner `Chain 02`
+- `selected/chain-03.md` contains planner `Chain 03`

